    <h3>Flights to Tokyo</h3>
    <p>Tokyo, the capital of Japan, is a dynamic, futuristic, and culturally rich city that blends tradition and innovation. Known for its sleek skyscrapers, ancient temples, and vibrant pop culture, Tokyo is a fascinating destination for travelers interested in experiencing both the past and the future.</p>

    <h4>Key Information:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Overview:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Location:</strong> Tokyo is located on the eastern coast of Japan, facing the Pacific Ocean.</li>
                <li><strong>Population:</strong> With over 13 million residents, Tokyo is one of the most populous cities in the world.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Famous Landmarks:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Tokyo Tower:</strong> A symbol of Tokyo, inspired by the Eiffel Tower, offering panoramic views of the city.</li>
                <li><strong>Shibuya Crossing:</strong> One of the busiest pedestrian crossings in the world.</li>
                <li><strong>Senso-ji Temple:</strong> The oldest temple in Tokyo, located in the Asakusa district.</li>
                <li><strong>Meiji Shrine:</strong> A serene and beautiful shrine located near Harajuku.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Cultural Experience:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Shopping:</strong> Tokyo offers an exciting shopping experience in districts like Harajuku, Shinjuku, and Ginza.</li>
                <li><strong>Food Culture:</strong> Tokyo is famous for its sushi, ramen, and cutting-edge cuisine.</li>
                <li><strong>Technology:</strong> Visit Akihabara, the mecca of electronics and anime culture.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
    
